Nevadans shouldn’t have to worry about whether they can afford housing during #COVID19. 

@SenCortezMasto and I are proud to announce over $2.6 million in housing support from CARES Act funding is coming to Nevada. 

https://t.co/4sTwtEQx4N

This is so important for our state. 

@SenCortezMasto and I were glad to announce an additional $74 million coming to Nevada’s health care providers to offset costs related to #COVID19 care.

https://t.co/kBcMsgTJ27

Our marijuana small businesses shouldn’t be left behind in our #COVID19 response. 

@RonWyden and I are leading our colleagues in calling on these businesses to have equal access to @SBAGov emergency loans and grants.

https://t.co/IEUkcOX9fD

As we all #StayHomeForNevada to combat #COVID19, domestic violence survivors are facing increased risks and support services are seeing increased need. 

@SenCortezMasto and I are calling for increased resources to protect survivors.

